(786, 'buton_description11', 'Branding is the promotional essential that has been there even before the advent of the Internet. It is a long way since the digital age crossed from the static and dreary classifieds of the print newspaper. Now, it is all about visuals, color schemes, codes, flashy pictures, and engaging videos. Here is an elaboration of some best kept secrets from Aztro Media that make us experts in the field.\r\nFirstly, we operate on the cognitive or emotional premise of branding. For one, promotions should be at once visually captivating, meaning that they incorporate personal or inanimate characteristics. Take for example the Safari app on the desktop. It incorporates a compass that characteristically impacts on the imagination as some application for finding direction or even exploring. Now, that is how our branding can strike your first time site visitors. \r\nBoy or girl, everyone has had some time to reflect on the poignant Apple trademarks. The logo in particular is an exquisite piece of simple, minimalist yet powerful art of an apple silhouette. The power of the branding lies in the visuals that each person can identify with. It is this kind of impact that our experts seek to portray in unique logo creations for multimedia brands and websites.\r\nFinally, we believe that marketing through branding should be a consistent experience that occurs through dynamic codes. We use HTML5 and CS3 scripts to map out visuals and text that can go through recycling. Whenever a webmaster wants to make a new logo, he or she does not have to install new software: they just need to modify the existing platform. The same case happens in video marketing, which is a very sensitive and often expensive tool for branding. We know how to retain old visuals and change them to suit the current needs of the user through the video appeal of such pictures. ', 'yes'),
