(338, 'blog_heading', 'Welcome To Aztro Media', 'yes'),
(339, 'blog_description', 'Experts in web development, social media, web solutions, WordPress, HTML5 and Cs3, as well as providers of unmatched marketing services. We do web development on a grafting platform, whereby we retain the core coding system of programming while incorporating novel functionality to suit unique websites for different businesses. In WordPress for example, our in-house team draws a wireframe of an entire blog, basing the skeleton on the core of the particular scripting language, before embedding unique codes and plugins.', 'yes'),
(659, '_site_transient_timeout_browser_f06ec280e9bf7a75da17008ecb37f3aa', '1356680963', 'yes'),
(340, 'blog_image', 'html-5.png', 'yes'),
(341, 'button_heading1', 'Merging iOS and Facebook', 'yes'),
(342, 'buton_description1', 'People talk of synchronization when what they mean is integration. Though Facebook syncs with many platforms and operating systems on the computer, it does this on a normal platter. It can work better through a special merger that makes it an extra part of an application. iOS-Facebook integration is such a marriage of sorts. It is possible to do this through simple steps that include authentication and plug-in troubleshooting before personalization of the new app. With it, notifications from friends will come specially, and publishing graphical fiction or diaries was never easier. ', 'yes'),
(343, 'button_heading2', 'Integrating Social Media Apps with Android', 'yes'),
(344, 'buton_description2', 'The term android gained first mass use in the short novel ‘Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?’ by Philip K. Dick in the 1960s. Since then, it has grown into the language, and even become more familiar through the Android smart phones. How better than to migrate to a Beta 3.0 with a Twitter/Facebook plug-in? Working with native applications of a handheld device is one thing and tempering them with novelty is another. That is why one can have desktop-like experience on their accounts on the native features of an android phone, together with matching Application Programming Interface (API) that automatically syncs with social media apps on this platform. After initializing the systems, you enjoy the pleasure of getting messages from friends like an SMS beep and will never miss a meeting just because the computer was far away to update scheduled appointments.', 'yes'),
(345, 'button_heading3', 'On-Site Social Media Customization', 'yes'),
(346, 'buton_description3', 'Since the advent of the big four, Facebook, Twitter, MySpace and LinkedIn, not mentioning a Chinese newcomer, social media has deprived websites their rightful user glory. Luckily, webmasters learnt long ago that there was a way out: either go to the portal and create company profile, or make Facebook come to the homepage. The benefits of the latter integration story are many. They include using the HTML advantages of a website to enable automatic on-site sign-ups. Secondly, followers can interact on the site at their will just like they do on their private accounts, which is a bonus to the user. Thirdly, it is possible to scrutinize the graphical interface of a given account holder, whose details can help customize how he or she relates to the webmaster.', 'yes'),
(347, 'button_heading4', 'Social Media: A Blessing or a Curse?', 'yes'),
(348, 'buton_description4', 'Social Media infiltrates the imagination with the fantastic yet mind-boggling world of the Internet. At other times, it mesmerizes with healthy gossip on the latest exploits of a corporate head, a fellow worker, a friend, classmate or family friend. To some, it acts as a stepping stone for amassing riches from the power of numbers: zillions of followers ready to pay anything to see a fan’s project get through. To others, it is all about the daily experience. It is a world on its own. They wake up Facebook, breakfast Twitter, lunch LinkedIn, dinner MySpace and sleep easily again on Facebook. So, is social media a blessing or a curse? It takes calculations on how many times the curser hovers over, ‘Mike wants to be Friends with you,’ ‘Accept Invite’ or ‘Like’ buttons, to tell. But businesses can rest easy because we know we can always use it as a blessing and turn in the profits. ', 'yes'),
(349, 'button_heading5', 'Social Media is a Person!', 'yes'),
(350, 'buton_description5', '1.	If the first thing before sleeping is checking latest account details before using the Smartphone as a pillow, and before brushing the teeth at dawn updating account information.\r\n2.	If it is impossible to live without a phone even for a day. Gadgets have become almost like lifelong bittersweet friends that avid Facebookers protect like pets.\r\n3.	If standing in the middle of the road, moving on from traffic a full minute after the rest of the cars have moved on either side, or crossing a busy thoroughfare when Facebooking is the case, then social media is indeed a person.', 'yes'),
(351, 'portfolio_heading', 'WEB PORTFOLIO', 'yes'),
(352, 'portfolio_subheading', 'Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem', 'yes'),
(353, 'title_but', 'our Web AppLication strengths are:', 'yes'),
(354, 'sub_title_but', 'Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem', 'yes'),
(355, 'hw_heading1', 'WE NEVER STOP INVENTING', 'yes'),
(356, 'hw_description1', 'Aztro Media works on an iterative basis, mainly hinging on intelligent analysis, developer-cum-private tests and optimization procedures. This follows closely on the heels of the initial research that goes into software development. While web development is complete in itself when executable software is ready for setting up on a consumer site it is however a step-by-step procedure. ', 'yes'),
(791, 'button_heading41', 'WORDPRESS', 'yes'),
(357, 'hw_heading2', 'Research', 'yes'),
(358, 'hw_description2', 'This is the conceptual stage where experts meet with and listen to a client’s visualization plan about any project they want modified or created. There is a wide range of schematic approaches to our research. One of this is through general guidelines surrounding web development that have passed the test of time. The other is the avante garde method, which though informal, produces much of the innovative products on the Internet today. Either of these methods incorporates the particulars of the client’s or customer’s site that will receive the installation. If it is in e-commerce, much of the concentration will go to business applications like CMS, as well as, monetization features. If it is in the arts and entertainment, most of the attention will figure largely on audio and video execution. There are other webmaster-centric ideas that we employ from a third-party point of view based on client requests. After the concept, there edges out a working shape on the canvas of our easel: the wireframe.', 'yes'),
(359, 'hw_heading3', 'Wireframe', 'yes'),
(360, 'hw_description3', 'To many, the wireframe is but a sketch to represent a deeper interaction. To us, a wireframe is more than a study of the content silo, user relations to the sketch and overall visual shape of a website or software. In it lies the silhouette of major details that will emerge in the final website or product. We try to make a hint of explanation on what lies beneath the mask by making the sketch more graphical, almost like a web portfolio.  \r\n \r\nIndeed, our wireframes are more akin to Leonardo da Vinci’s sketches on Sybil, which represent human anatomy at its clearest even without adding a daub of paint anywhere. We have a team of interactive designers whose duty is to tow the line between a shell of a site and the interactive part that will emerge fully at the prototype stage. Indeed, our wireframes consist of the underlying features of the software prototype that comes up next, namely: typography, sketchy navigation icons and function.', 'yes'),
(361, 'hw_heading4', 'Prototype', 'yes'),
(362, 'hw_description4', 'The early meaning of prototyping was to just present operational wireframes that anybody could use at an amateur stage rather than go hunting for complete examples elsewhere. At Aztro Media, we go a step further. We separate prototypes into a triple set. There is the Wireframe design already under the above explanation. But to us, it consists of self-driving functions, because the main idea is to have a shape of a product that is just on the verge of becoming something that a user can ‘drive’ but not quite for use.  \r\n \r\nThe next prototype is that of visual objects that we display on the screen using vendor programs for drawing photos and making videos. Understandably, these products are accessible to most end-users and therefore quite easy to experiment with. Here, the undertaking becomes an orderly trial and error venture, which from a developer’s perspective will bring cost-effective results. It is simple and easy to deploy for it necessitates no extra IT brains.  \r\n \r\nThen there is the very interactive design, which is our hallmark. It is a package that allows users to have an innovative plug-in. A basic example is that of the Android Sandwich operating system which is available on Amazon tablets for hacker-developers to experiment on. In other words, our exclusive prototype acts as a place for coming up with something new that is the beginning of the long relationship between an interactive website/product and the user.', 'yes'),
(363, 'hw_heading5', 'Test', 'yes'),
(364, 'hw_description5', 'Testing software is one of the all-important goals of execution. It implies four things: first, finding out, practically, whether it has grown up to the conceptual and design expectations. Secondly, troubleshooting it to know whether it operates exactly as the developer or end-user would have liked. Thirdly, if it can go into production stage under the current features and finally, the reaction it derives from clients, users and other experts. As professional prototype providers, we double up on our duties.  \r\n \r\nWe can conduct impartial inquiry for third-party clients on the suitability of software that another agency has made for them or make our own tests into the workable nature of a product that has gone under development in-house. In the first instance, we use a rule book to compare what the clients wanted of the developer, point by point, against the half-finished product under test. In the second instance, we belabor ourselves under the same point-by-point procedure. We also concentrate on one of the most important goals of any testing, which is to check the anti-virus stability of the interactive specimen we have just made.', 'yes'),
(365, 'hw_heading6', 'Deploy', 'yes'),
(366, 'hw_description6', 'To deploy means many things. It is not just setting up software nor is it just confirming that the system has initialized on the other end after turning off and on the computer. Rather, it is bridging the divide between the tested, now complete product and the ecosystem on which it will operate. Though a program on a CD is the culmination of the developer’s idea, in portable form, it is not a program unless it operates on an interface that supports it. For this, we first install the prototype on our own site to check its viability. We then transfer it to the client’s site after checking that all systems on the other side are in supporting mode. If they are not, we install the lacking parameters or even suggest what the user needs (normal Internet files usually call for download of related software).  \r\n \r\nThe next step is to execute the file in its new home. This implies opening up all its nodes to comply with an automatic feature that activates it. We also provide a feature of deactivation in case one feels that they no longer need the installation on the computer. The final stages are essentially later and timely. One of these is modifying the software to suit modern usage. There is also the updating feature that allows the product to reach the quality of new programs in the market.', 'yes'),
(367, 'hw_heading7', 'Optimize', 'yes'),
(368, 'hw_description7', 'This step needs a preamble for better comprehension. Web geeks have noted over time that whenever major software works in different devices it necessitates some modification. This implies decreasing its memory consumption though a slower delivery or hiking its time of deployment when there is sufficient memory to support this fast installation. In short, to optimize is to partially modify rather than wholly modify. We at Aztro Media believe that there is no way that an entire program can undergo equal overhaul. When one side is working optimally, the other is working normally. To work normally is not ideal to many. They seek it to meet some ultra level of performance to suit their given environment of operation. This is why we help clients control one or two sides of a program to help them realize their goals. It might be that our experts can improve the time one spends to deploy. It might also be that we can depreciate energy use in a product drastically by making it faster in implementation. It might also be that our team can compress a memory-consuming part of a program and help a phone user view any heavy stuff on a computer. This in other words is post-deployment modification or optimization.', 'yes'),
(1082, 'newsletter_logger_secret', 'd074ff5a', 'yes'),
(369, 'hw_heading8', 'Monitor', 'yes'),
(370, 'hw_description8', 'If a client goes into trouble with an installation, the Aztro team will rush in and configure the systems again. Network maintenance is also another essential ingredient of monitoring because it helps to improve the unity between the various parts of a software deployment system. The entire system should be a self-sufficient fabric but with such an engineering redundancy that if one part fails, it only denies the inherent function but does not lead to system collapse. Monitoring can also be a follow-up dispensation just after the body of work in a project is over. It can also be a perpetual procedure that involves daily remote and on-premise monitoring, especially for big organizations that depend on their virtual interfaces. Our service can also be occasional whereby we operate on an ‘as is’ basis.', 'yes'),
(371, 'hw_heading', '', 'yes'),
