r to web developer within the past 5 years and has been working with WordPress since version 2.2. He has a passion for picking up web technologies and programming and focuses on being the complete developer. <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/2012/12/03/welcome-tom-carney/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"April Heline";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1243:"<p>We have had a very busy year at WebDevStudios and in order to better serve our clients and continue to build awesome things the WebDevStudios team is growing again! We would like to welcome Tom Carney to the family!</p>\n<p>Tom has been working to evolve from a web designer to web developer within the past 5 years and has been working with WordPress since version 2.2. He has a passion for picking up web technologies and programming and focuses on being the complete developer.</p>\n<p>Recently, Tom has been focusing on expanding his BuddyPress knowledge. He recently gave a <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/thomascarney/buddy-press-10192012#btnNext" target="_blank">presentation</a> on BuddyPress at WordCamp Philly with Brian Messenlehner.</p>\n<p>Tom is joining WebDevStudios as our newest developer and will be focusing on client work and BuddyPress development. <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/" target="_blank">Brian</a> is excited to add Tom and his BuddyPress expertise to our team.</p>\n<p>We are happy to have Tom on the team and can&#8217;t wait to put him to work! Find out more about Tom on our <a title="Tom Carney" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/tom-carney/">team page</a>.</p>\n<div></div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s