ps://twitter.com/dremeda">Dre Armeda</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/ryanimel">Ryan Imel</a> and WebDevStudios&#8217; <a href="https://twitter.com/williamsba">Brad Williams</a>. Each week the guys sit down (sometime with a special guest!) and discuss current events in the WordPress world such as WordPress updates, new products, WordCamps, and more.</p>\n<p>WP Late Night is certainly not your average tech podcast. The hosts say that WP Late Night is <em>the closest you can get to a WordCamp after party, in handy podcast form </em>and this is no exaggeration. Along with normal WordPress chat there are plenty of beers, sound effects, costume changes and all around tomfoolery.</p>\n<p>Get in on the WP Late Night action by joining in the <a href="http://wpcandy.com/stream">live interactive chat</a>. Find out about upcoming episodes on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/WpLateNight">Facebook</a> or at <a href="http://wplatenight.com">WPLateNight.com</a> and listen in live on the <a href="http://wpcandy.com/stream">WP Candy livestream</a>.</p>\n<p><span style="line-height: 24px;">Missed out on the live recording? Tune in to the latest episode (or any past episode) on </span><a style="line-height: 24px;" href="http://www.youtube.com/user/wpcandydotcom/videos?view=0">YouTube</a><span style="line-height: 24px;">, </span><a style="line-height: 24px;" href="http://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/wp-late-night/id496147707">iTunes</a><span style="line-height: 24px;">, or download the </span><a style="line-height: 24px;" href="http://wpcandy.com/category/broadcasts/wp-late-night">MP3 file</a><span style="line-height: 24px;">.</span></p>\n<h3><strong>WP Late Night airs live every Wednesday at 8pm Eastern. <a href="http://wpcandy.com/stream">Tune in tonight!</a></strong></h3>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://webdevstud