(788, 'buton_description21', 'One of the most important steps in web development and the one that is visually relevant is web design. It is no wonder then that at Aztro Media, this is a huge process that undergoes several iterations. It is all about the understanding of the relationship between the hidden structure of a site and the discernable page layout. In other words, we create an infrastructure silo between the navigable software and the graphical interface consisting of the homepage, web portfolio and page layout. Which steps do we follow to accomplish our missions?\r\nWe begin with the artistic concept. This is known as the proprietary phase. A web designer comes in, studies a client’s vision for his/her website and comes up with an initial blueprint. This forms what we call the wireframe. It is a fruit of wide-ranging research on a particular website project and a borrowing of standard skeletons of existing sites that have a particular layout. For a site to be user-friendly, it must have a wireframe that is from the point of view of the viewer. This is what we call the prototype.\r\nFor prototype, our experts consider several layout angles. Is the header appropriate the way it is? Could the web portfolio at the top need more graphical colors or is it appropriate as it is? Could the tabs for various topics become more navigable if they could move to one side of the homepage rather than on the top bar? Finally, we come up with a partially fulfilling web design based on a prototype that the user can modify later at ease.\r\nFor web design to reach its intuitive end, it requires a powerful user interface that incorporates, among others, the following details according to profession. If it is an e-commerce blog, we can use user-friendly WordPress CMS. If it is a video sharing site, we incorporate ad technology at the bottom of the screen to pop before the viewer’s eye without hindering content. In short, web design at Aztro Media is all about an iterative process, the end-user and the profession.', 'yes'),
(789, 'button_heading31', 'WEB APPLICATIONS', 'yes'),
(790, 'buton_description31', 'Web application development should be strong and dynamic. In fact the Internet as we know it could be but a shell for keeping military information if it were not for the rise of apps. It is these applications that conjoin different codes, markup scripts and other core structures that unify the web for harmonized access, reading, updating, exchange and retrieval of data at the click of the mouse. At Aztro Media, web applications are more than the app store favorites: we go the extra mile to bring open source stats home.\r\nHTML5 is one of the new kids on the block that we just cannot ignore. Though it is still in perpetual development phases, as of 2012, we still consider it a dynamic multi-device programming platform that suits most clients. It seamlessly melts physical and technological boundaries between phones and computers. Furthermore, the deployment of this language is not as hard as it sounds. It just requires updating, without setting up new plugins, on an existing HTML interface. It is indeed an overgrowth, open source markup script from HTML.\r\nAnother essential web application that our experts are savvy with is CS3. This master app by Adobe consists of more than a dozen internal editions. Though the expertise of an IT department par excellence, clients get to experience the one-on-one interactivity of CS3. It might be integrating all videos on a Mac device into one, changing the timeline on a music clip in an editing room or just help boost the operational delivery of one of the supported browsing networks. This is the tool to incorporate.\r\nOur team takes several masterly steps when incorporating new web applications. The first is research on viability. The second is to devise a plan on implementation after coming up with a suitable app. This includes defining the role the application will play in concrete terms. If it is a file sharing software we say so. The planning phase also includes user terms including who is eligible to access the code, and also how eligible operators can employ the device. Finally comes the deployment phase (web development stage) that is followed by a monitoring time. This is all that accounts for the integrity of web applications on the web let alone a particular website.', 'yes'),
(792, 'buton_description41', 'WordPress is one of the leading language platforms for hosting an ecommerce blog, enabled by its highly compatible Customer Relationship Management software. Here at Aztro Media, we ensure that what you get as a client is something original, i.e. sharing the core structure of the program, but unique as well.\r\nWe share in the creation of plug-ins that can revolutionize online business because they fine-tune applications to the particular programming desire of the website niche. In case the client does not want to delegate language coding to outsource partners, we can alternatively offer time-tested guidelines on how to write a plug-in. Other learning spheres about WordPress include a page on how to uphold the best standards for the program. There is also a section that offers tips on how to debug this markup structure using in-house WordPress technology to do so.\r\nOur services do not just concern the end-consumer alone or a corporate website. We also extend details to vendors who want to create a plug-in on the WordPress platform and distribute the prototype, far and wide. This will not only earn them recognition as developers but will enhance the promotion agility for their new products. In a world where thousands of applications are receiving a facelift every day, it behooves a developer to look for a team like Aztro Media to help promote a new plug-in.\r\nThe most important dispensation lies in incorporating any new system that WordPress comes up with. If it is a migration platform to help launch a prototype from one version of the language to another, we are here with wide open arms to guide in the transition. Setting WordPress to classic Application Programming Interfaces that are already supporting the program is also one of our key proficiencies. Indeed, anything that helps your website make the best leverage on past and new versions of WordPress can easily be brought to life by our inspired team.\r\n', 'yes'),
(793, 'button_heading51', 'E-COMMERCE', 'yes'),
(794, 'buton_description51', 'E-commerce is more than shopping carts, monetization and online credit card transactions. There is more than meets the eye.\r\nAre you wallowing in the mire of a static, rigid, redundant and unqualified e-commerce tool that troubleshoots when deploying? Aztro Media is a development firm that not only configures e-commerce solutions for websites, but helps shop around for the most suitable widgets to help keep customers in a well-rounded order page.\r\nOur open source e-commerce solutions straddle the worlds of premium and basic. Premium vaunts a range of offerings that conform to the functional and architectural role of an e-commerce tool in a business page. It is functional because the user has sufficient ability to use it any way they want and architectural because it appears on a page strategically just like a coupon, requiring but a click to initiate settings, leading to a transaction. Premium solutions are also 100% flexible over any technology, domain and safety protocol. The tools also synchronize trouble-free, unlike common apps from e-Commerce stores. \r\nIf you scour through the dozens of e-Commerce projects we have developed on the Big Spider, you will be surprised at the news of easy cost from clients who have applied the basic solution packages. Indeed, our basic solutions are not just budget-worthy but possess uptime. They deploy fast, which minus the trial period, drastically decreases the time one spends installing such apps. \r\nTaking the powerful combination of budget-worthy offerings, fast turnaround in deployment, and dual choice of packaged solutions, whether premium or basic, Aztro Media’s e-Commerce development offer is complete in itself.', 'yes'),
(908, 'onM_button_heading41', 'Online Marketing on the Go', 'yes'),
(911, 'onM_buton_description31', 'Google is the number one site on the Internet. According to many, it is also a resourceful online marketing page because it has its own custom approaches to web marketing. One of these is Google AdWords, not forgetting Google+. While the former is savvier to the ad-production campaign, the latter is more social on its premise. At a time when they are offering contests for thousands of learners from a century of nations, to produce innovative web promotion concepts that can earn users rewards, it was high time that webmasters employed some of the offerings of this portal to reach to more users.  Not only is the site a good place to start a campaign for product recognition through the YouTube Broadcast Yourself, it is also a place to learn more about online marketing through its search engine guidelines.', 'yes'),
(912, 'onM_onM_button_heading41', 'Online Marketing on the Go', 'yes'),
(913, 'onM_buton_description41', 'One of the offshoots of Web 2.0., with the support of such omnipresent applications like HTML5, is the migration of computer technology onto phones. In early days, it was hard to dream of using phones to perform registration details or even advertising from home. Nowadays, not only can one do raw functions of a computer on a Smartphone (due to JavaScript), but can perform the duty more easily though compatible media that has gone through modification to support cross-gadget functions. There are various apps that are developing primarily for phone-based web marketing. These lay their premise on open source technologies like HTML5 that can bring necessary software like Customer Relationship Management to the phone and so forth. Thus, it is possible to perform business operation, advertise and stay in touch with consumers via efficient methods like email lists, on the go.', 'yes'),
(909, 'onM_button_heading51', 'Where Article Submission Meets online Marketing', 'yes'),
(910, 'onM_buton_description51', 'Sending articles in bulk to a portal is not just to inform the Internet or going public that there exists a powerful authority on a given topic. Rather, it is also a versatile marketing weapon that aims to entice both search engines to find a site, and other webmasters to interlink with the article source. Though quality is a primary drive of much of the content in directories, quantity also matters if online marketing will reach its technical end: saturation. Saturation refers to indexing on the Big Spider by crawlers depending on the volume of output on select keywords. If the major phrase is ‘video editing’ and a site devotes ten pages to it, and another devotes just one, then it follows that the saturation ranking of the former outstrips the latter’s. It is the power of content via the authoritativeness, the linking promise, together with its accessibility by engine tools that makes article submission a worthy player in the online marketing milieu. It not only gives a name to the marketer, but leaves the site’s name climbing high in the directory via the links and author’s bio that the piece incorporates. ', 'yes'),
(799, 'title_but2', 'our Web AppLication strengths are:', 'yes'),
(800, 'sub_title_but2', 'Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem', 'yes'),
(801, 'button_heading12', 'Why SEO Affiliation is Still King of Organic Marketing', 'yes'),
(802, 'buton_description12', 'Talk about SEO and the first thing that pops to mind is that of a very honest webmaster relying on page layout, keyword optimization and links with syndicates to generate traffic. One can also peer, by way of passing, into the inevitably interlinked white trick and black hat anathema. What people fail to see at first glance however is the power of affiliate marketing. No money changes hands to advertise content but a simple, informed description of a product in any marketing website to earn the marketer some bucks for the leads these reviews bring home to the manufacturer. It still matches up to its original name as a marketing campaign that hinges on organic protocols.', 'yes'),
(803, 'button_heading22', 'Back End Analytics', 'yes'),
(804, 'buton_description22', 'One of the most practical ways for ardent SEO enthusiasts to underscore their sites’ performance on the Internet is to use back end analytical icons. These tools help to analyze, via mathematical formulas, exactly how many keywords a site needs to attract attention of the bots, and the number of texts it requires to hit saturation in the indexes. There is also an important aspect, that of HTML coding. The better the site’s background script, the more navigational it becomes and hence the improvement in its search value. Some experts query whether this is genuine SEO marketing but some parameters indicate that it is. No ads are involved, nor any poaching of links: most users of analytics rely on back links. The only seeming crime, here, is doing the duty of a search engine by arranging keywords, texts and back links in exacting numbers. Still, so long as content is relevant to niche and no white hat tricks are apparent anywhere, there is no reason why this should not rank as SEO marketing.', 'yes'),
(805, 'button_heading32', 'Data Conversion through Coding for SEO', 'yes'),
(806, 'buton_description32', 'Due to the sophistication of the Internet in the wake of many protocols that have come up to improve and justify ranking by merit, webmasters are getting smarter with the art of SEO. They also collide with the crawlers in their own backyard by coercing with JavaScript and other codes. These instantly inform them about the hits to the site, as well as, which exact SEO parameter has converted most traffic for the day. They also highlight programming features, often affecting the visibility of a site. For example, a webmaster may find that he or she has done every internal and external optimization work but still the level of traffic is at a low, only to find out through a spy code that a hidden part of the site is crawling while the rest is navigable. Overhauling this overlooked part can help create better, more unified conversion rate for the site.', 'yes'),
(807, 'button_heading42', 'Why Panda and Penguin will Always Loom large in SEO Marketing', 'yes'),
(808, 'buton_description42', 'The basic premise of SEO is visibility that can turn popularity into marketing gain. If a lead turns into a potential customer, well and good. But if on the other hand penalization for turning a lead into a customer through a black hat trick comes to be, too bad. Indeed Panda which checks the inclusiveness of the information silo on the site in all its parts, ranging from keywords to content (both text and images), is a force to reckon with in genuine marketing. It highlights all the bad sectors that need overhaul before ranking that is based on keyword prowess can turn into a lead. With Penguin, SEO marketing turns a mature page when it comes to proper linking. Days are gone when link poaching was the in-thing. It was not unusual to stumble upon a site whose majority of links were either dead ends or had nothing to do with the website itself. Planning on how to use keywords and links is a professional endeavor. It is a life and death matter for an organic site that relies on its customer base to turn its fortune without including ads to support its goals.', 'yes'),
(809, 'button_heading52', 'Article Submission', 'yes'),
(810, 'buton_description52', 'One of the most popular inclusions in an SEO package by providers is that of committing to submit informative articles to an article directory regularly. These texts come from shining stars of prose and research. Not only is there high quality nature in the writ, but each piece bears with it a bio of the site master. Secondly, search engines pay constant visits to these portals where they find a lot of keywords that can directly or accidentally earn the site a few visits from interested surfers. Thirdly, there is the syndication marvel that comes to those with wonderful stories that other webmasters want to link to. This, at the end of the day, leads to a lot of connivance between site masters, where some of whom want permanent links and others reciprocal links.\r\n\r\nIn most cases, directories are one-stop shops for both surfers and the browsing networks. They facilitate inclusion of all text appearing under similar theme into one master file that end-users via search engines can filter. Furthermore, it is genuine marketing, objectively speaking, because it makes for a competitive marketplace where quantitative and qualitative aspects of article submission count as the determinants of a site’s success.', 'yes'),
(849, 'sub_title_but_social_m', 'Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem', 'yes'),
(848, 'title_but_social_m', 'our Web AppLication strengths are:', 'yes'),
(850, 'button_heading_social_m1', 'Grow Exponentially Via Social Media Maintenance', 'yes'),
(851, 'buton_description_social_m1', 'Statistics from a 2011 survey showed that social media maintenance helped boost the leads to order and networking pages of businesses which had initiated the campaign by a staggering 300 percent. This at least helps to unmask the simple reasoning that Facebook or Twitter is just for interaction. There is a brave new world of maintenance that alone can keep the profile visible to both target audiences (T/A) and potential customers. This is why implementing services like constant updating, answering ‘likes’ professionally, captioning videos properly and deleting negative comments in time, are quite important for a thriving company that drives its traffic through its profile.', 'yes'),
(852, 'button_heading_social_m2', 'Social Media Maintenance an Industry in Itself', 'yes'),
(853, 'buton_description_social_m2', 'By 2012, 89 percent of businesses were using social networking in one way or another. A revolutionary wind is blowing their way, however, in the name of the social media maintenance industry. It is a situation where the author of a diary gets an adviser who guides on proper diction, updated profiles, and competitive challenges for group members in a profile, and also undertaking branding campaigns on their behalf. The profile page in Facebook is one of the most important eye-openers for the first-time follower of an entity or individual. That is why it requires a charmingly professional tone. Some choose to make it lurid while others go the enticing way. It requires professionals to keep updating this data, with changing times, and only by selecting a partner to take social media maintenance as a separate department can this happen.', 'yes'),
(854, 'button_heading_social_m3', 'What Social Media Maintenance Packages Have In Common', 'yes'),
(855, 'buton_description_social_m3', 'There is a commonplace agreement in everything tempered with a few differences here and there. Most major social media maintenance packages usually collide in their service dispensation but differ on pricing. The most typical offerings in the basic and exclusive packages include the following: \r\n•	Background check on profile, together with a seven-day Facebook/Twitter update. For exclusive deals this can reach to a single update on the status every 24 hours.\r\n•	A 30-day blog write up for SEO posting. In exclusive deals this can go up to four posts, each month.\r\n•	Differences include pricing which in most cases go to $50 for the simplest packages and $250 to $350 for advanced packages. \r\nHere at Aztro we have the budget-worthy $199.99 exclusive deal. ', 'yes'),
(856, 'button_heading_social_m4', 'Get Authoritative Social Media Maintenance Grip: Training', 'yes'),
(857, 'buton_description_social_m4', 'To prove that social media maintenance is becoming a necessity to corporate entities online, a new training system has emerged. It helps webmasters operating sites of their companies know, among others, how to post messages that attract a horde of commentators. For example, users can know how short messages with less than 140 characters, solidified by a captivating image, can attract almost anyone’s comment. Training on social media maintenance also means knowing the best frequency for blog posting for followers, how to detect and eliminate spamming altogether, and using SEO to market videos on one’s profile page.', 'yes'),
(858, 'button_heading_social_m5', 'Fan Base Maintenance Via Social Media', 'yes'),
(859, 'buton_description_social_m5', 'It takes a lengthy time for one man to reconnoiter what the rest of the industry is exactly doing and help connect with them through their own visions. To facilitate this burning of bridges and becoming one, social media maintenance can help glean facts about a website or another entity in the sector, create content relating to it and send them a relevant invitation based on this research. The maintenance of a fan base also means publishing constant messages on special occasions, coming up with new productions, and posting thoughts for the day. All this does not have to be a personal burden. As a profile owner concentrates on pressuring business, the maintenance experts do the honors for him or her on the other side of the screen.', 'yes'),
