(903, 'onM_button_heading11', 'Web 2.0 in Pay Per Click Online Marketing', 'yes'),
(904, 'onM_buton_description11', 'Before the advent of Web 2.0 in 2004, most of the reins of Internet content were in the hands of a select few webmasters. Now almost every amateur producer who uploads a video on YouTube can edit, modify and earn revenue from it via clicks. Pay per Click has become a savvy ad-conversion technology that does not exclude the basic technical skills of most web rookies, who are often having their first such interaction with the commercial side of the Internet. PPC should not only be technically feasible. It should also work in terms of converting revenue for every click that a visitor makes for the creator of the promotional material. In these days, it is rare that video content in particular should go without an ad to whet the senses of the bored viewer of the video. These ads can appear anywhere including as pop up messages on users’ email addresses, WebPages and also portals for video sharing. The most important goal of a web marketer is to optimize all the ads and make them pop up where they are necessary. For example, if an email address profiles much correspondence on book publication deals, then eBook marketers can take advantage. They can optimize their PPC campaign on these pages, using Web 2.0 efficiency for micro posting.', 'yes'),
(905, 'onM_button_heading21', 'Facebook: The second Best Platform to do Web Marketing', 'yes'),
(906, 'onM_buton_description21', 'One can learn many things about Facebook at a glance, all inextricably tied to marketing. First of all, being the largest social media site in the world, it has over eight hundred million subscribers, a market and a half to exploit. It is also effectively the number two most popular page to land on, after that of Google. This is reason enough to believe that searches of online content start here. Going into internal analytics, one realizes that the median user of the social platform has a follower base of 130 pals. Individually, he or she contributes to the nine hundred thousand correspondences that pass through the platform per day, and also may form part of the two hundred and fifty thousand contemporary subscribers who use handheld devices to log in. Starting from the latter point, it is apparent that, proportionally, those who sign in on their smart phones are more likely to do business on Facebook by double the margin of those who use computers. There are also quite many ways to utilize this social media page for business dealings, including the publication of serial messages that thousands can comment on, posting business announcements, and also advertising via links that users can link back to from their own sites.', 'yes'),
